Senator Ahmad Lawan, representing Yobe North, has been elected as Senate President. Lawan defeated Senator Ali-Ndume with 79 votes, out of the total of 107 votes cast. Lawan emerges having scored a total vote of 79. He defeated his co contender, former Senate President for the 9th Senate, Senator Ali Ndume, APC, Borno South. Ndume polled 28 Votes.  Announcing the result, the Clerk to the National Assembly, CNA, Mohammed Sani Omolori said that 107 Senators- elect voted. Lawan was immediately sworn in by the CNA after taking the oath of allegiance and that of office.